45 inline bool IsWhitespace(char c)
46 {
47  return (c == ' ') || (c == '\t');
48 }
49 
50 inline bool IsSeparator(char c)
51 {
52  return IsWhitespace(c) || (c == ':') || (c == '|') || (c == ',');
53 }

55 inline bool StrEqualsNocase(std::string const & s1, std::string const & s2)
56 {
57  if (s1.size() != s2.size()) { return false; }
58  for (size_t i = 0; i < s1.size(); ++i)
59  {
60  if (tolower(s1[i]) != tolower(s2[i])) { return false; }
61  }
62  return true;
63 }

78 void Parser::ProcessCurrentLine()
79 {
80  if (m_in_block_comment)
81  {
82  if (StrEqualsNocase(m_current_line, "end_comment"))
83  {
84  m_in_block_comment = false;
85  }
86  return;
87  }
88  else if (StrEqualsNocase(m_current_line, "comment"))
89  {
90  m_in_block_comment = true;
91  return;
92  }
93  else if (m_in_description_section) // Enter logic is below in 'keywords'
94  {
95  if (StrEqualsNocase(m_current_line, "end_description"))
96  {
97  m_in_description_section = false;
98  }
99  else
100  {
101  m_definition->description.push_back(m_current_line);
102  }
103  return;
104  }
105  else if ((m_current_line[0] == ';') || (m_current_line[0] == '/'))
106  {
107  return;
108  }
109 
110  this->TokenizeCurrentLine();
111 
112  // Detect keywords on current line
113  File::Keyword keyword = IdentifyKeywordInCurrentLine();
114  switch (keyword)
115  {
116  case File::KEYWORD_INVALID: break; // No new section - carry on with processing data

294 bool Parser::CheckNumArguments(int num_required_args)
295 {
296  if (num_required_args > m_num_args)
297  {
298  char msg[200];
299  snprintf(msg, 200, "Not enough arguments, %d required, got %d. Skipping line.", num_required_args, m_num_args);
300  this->AddMessage(Message::TYPE_WARNING, msg);
301  return false;
302  }
303  return true;
304 }

316 void Parser::ParseWing()
317 {
318  if (!this->CheckNumArguments(16)) { return; }
319 
320  Wing wing;
321 
322  for (int i = 0; i < 8; i++) { wing.nodes[i] = this->GetArgNodeRef (i); }
323  for (int i = 8; i < 16; i++) { wing.tex_coords[i-8] = this->GetArgFloat (i); }
324 
325  if (m_num_args > 16) { wing.control_surface = this->GetArgWingSurface (16); }
326  if (m_num_args > 17) { wing.chord_point = this->GetArgFloat (17); }
327  if (m_num_args > 18) { wing.min_deflection = this->GetArgFloat (18); }
328  if (m_num_args > 19) { wing.max_deflection = this->GetArgFloat (19); }
329  if (m_num_args > 20) { wing.airfoil = this->GetArgStr (20); }
330  if (m_num_args > 21) { wing.efficacy_coef = this->GetArgFloat (21); }
331 
332  m_current_module->wings.push_back(wing);
333 }

423 void Parser::ParseTractionControl()
424 {
425  Ogre::StringVector tokens = Ogre::StringUtil::split(m_current_line + 15, ","); // "TractionControl" = 15 characters
426  if (tokens.size() < 2)
427  {
428  this->AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Too few arguments");
429  return;
430  }
431 
432  TractionControl tc;
433  tc.regulation_force = this->ParseArgFloat(tokens[0].c_str());
434  tc.wheel_slip = this->ParseArgFloat(tokens[1].c_str());
435  if (tokens.size() > 2) { tc.fade_speed = this->ParseArgFloat(tokens[2].c_str()); }
436  if (tokens.size() > 3) { tc.pulse_per_sec = this->ParseArgFloat(tokens[3].c_str()); }
437 
438  for (unsigned int i=4; i<tokens.size(); i++)
439  {
440  Ogre::StringVector args2 = Ogre::StringUtil::split(tokens[i], ":");
441  Ogre::StringUtil::trim(args2[0]);
442  Ogre::StringUtil::toLowerCase(args2[0]);
443 
444  if (args2[0] == "mode" && args2.size() == 2)
445  {
446  Ogre::StringVector attrs = Ogre::StringUtil::split(args2[1], "&");
447  auto itor = attrs.begin();
448  auto endi = attrs.end();
449  for (; itor != endi; ++itor)
450  {
451  std::string attr = *itor;
452  Ogre::StringUtil::trim(attr);
453  Ogre::StringUtil::toLowerCase(attr);
454  if (strncmp(attr.c_str(), "nodash", 6) == 0) { tc.attr_no_dashboard = true; }
455  else if (strncmp(attr.c_str(), "notoggle", 8) == 0) { tc.attr_no_toggle = true; }
456  else if (strncmp(attr.c_str(), "on", 2) == 0) { tc.attr_is_on = true; }
457  else if (strncmp(attr.c_str(), "off", 3) == 0) { tc.attr_is_on = false; }
458  }
459  }
460  else
461  {
462  this->AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, "TractionControl Mode: missing");
463  tc.attr_no_dashboard = false;
464  tc.attr_no_toggle = false;
465  tc.attr_is_on = true;
466  }
467  }
468 
469  if (m_current_module->traction_control != nullptr)
470  {
471  this->AddMessage(Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Multiple inline-sections 'TractionControl' in a module, using last one ...");
472  }
473 
474  m_current_module->traction_control = std::shared_ptr<TractionControl>( new TractionControl(tc) );
475 }

580 void Parser::_ParseNodeOptions(unsigned int & options, const std::string & options_str)
581 {
582  options = 0;
583 
584  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < options_str.length(); i++)
585  {
586  const char c = options_str.at(i);
587  switch(c)
588  {
589  case 'l':
590  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_l_LOAD_WEIGHT);
591  break;
592  case 'n':
593  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_n_MOUSE_GRAB);
594  BITMASK_SET_0(options, Node::OPTION_m_NO_MOUSE_GRAB);
595  break;
596  case 'm':
597  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_m_NO_MOUSE_GRAB);
598  BITMASK_SET_0(options, Node::OPTION_n_MOUSE_GRAB);
599  break;
600  case 'f':
601  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_f_NO_SPARKS);
602  break;
603  case 'x':
604  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_x_EXHAUST_POINT);
605  break;
606  case 'y':
607  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_y_EXHAUST_DIRECTION);
608  break;
609  case 'c':
610  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_c_NO_GROUND_CONTACT);
611  break;
612  case 'h':
613  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_h_HOOK_POINT);
614  break;
615  case 'e':
616  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_e_TERRAIN_EDIT_POINT);
617  break;
618  case 'b':
619  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_b_EXTRA_BUOYANCY);
620  break;
621  case 'p':
622  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_p_NO_PARTICLES);
623  break;
624  case 'L':
625  BITMASK_SET_1(options, Node::OPTION_L_LOG);
626  break;
627 
628  default:
629  this->AddMessage(options_str, Message::TYPE_WARNING, std::string("Ignoring invalid option: ") + c);
630  break;
631  }
632  }
633 }

664 void Parser::ParseDirectiveSetBeamDefaults()
665 {
666  if (! this->CheckNumArguments(2)) { return; } // 2 items: keyword, arg
667 
668  BeamDefaults d(*m_user_beam_defaults);
669 
670  // What's the state of "enable_advanced_deformation" feature at this point?
671  // Directive "enable_advanced_deformation" alters the effects of BeamDefaults
672  // Since the old parser worked on-the-fly, only BeamDefaults defined after the directive were affected
673 
674  d._enable_advanced_deformation = m_definition->enable_advanced_deformation;
675 
676  d._is_user_defined = true; //The "_enable_advanced_deformation" must only be aplied to user-defined values, not defaults.
677  d.springiness = this->GetArgFloat(1);
678 
679  if (m_num_args > 2) { d.damping_constant = this->GetArgFloat(2); }
680  if (m_num_args > 3) { d.deformation_threshold = this->GetArgFloat(3); }
681  if (m_num_args > 4) { d.breaking_threshold = this->GetArgFloat(4); }
682  if (m_num_args > 5) { d.visual_beam_diameter = this->GetArgFloat(5); }
683  if (m_num_args > 6) { d.beam_material_name = this->GetArgStr (6); }
684  if (m_num_args > 7) { d.plastic_deform_coef = this->GetArgFloat(7); }
685 
686  if (m_num_args > 7 && d.plastic_deform_coef >= 0.0f) { d._is_plastic_deform_coef_user_defined = true; }
687 
688  if (d.springiness < 0.f) { d.springiness = DEFAULT_SPRING; }
689  if (d.damping_constant < 0.f) { d.damping_constant = DEFAULT_DAMP; }
690  if (d.deformation_threshold < 0.f) { d.deformation_threshold = BEAM_DEFORM; }
691  if (d.breaking_threshold < 0.f) { d.breaking_threshold = BEAM_BREAK; }
692  if (d.visual_beam_diameter < 0.f) { d.visual_beam_diameter = DEFAULT_BEAM_DIAMETER; }
693  if (d.plastic_deform_coef < 0.f) { d.plastic_deform_coef = (*m_user_beam_defaults).plastic_deform_coef; }
694 
695  m_user_beam_defaults = std::shared_ptr<BeamDefaults>( new BeamDefaults(d) );
696  return;

815 void Parser::ParseHook()
816 {
817  if (! this->CheckNumArguments(1)) { return; }
818 
819  Hook hook;
820  hook.node = this->GetArgNodeRef(0);
821 
822  int i = 1;
823  while (i < m_num_args)
824  {
825  std::string attr = this->GetArgStr(i);
826  Ogre::StringUtil::trim(attr);
827  const bool has_value = (i < (m_num_args - 1));
828 
829  // Values
830  if (has_value && (attr == "hookrange") ) { hook.option_hook_range = this->GetArgFloat(++i); }
831  else if (has_value && (attr == "speedcoef") ) { hook.option_speed_coef = this->GetArgFloat(++i); }
832  else if (has_value && (attr == "maxforce") ) { hook.option_max_force = this->GetArgFloat(++i); }
833  else if (has_value && (attr == "timer") ) { hook.option_timer = this->GetArgFloat(++i); }
834  else if (has_value && (attr == "hookgroup" || attr == "hgroup") ) { hook.option_hookgroup = this->GetArgInt (++i); }
835  else if (has_value && (attr == "lockgroup" || attr == "lgroup") ) { hook.option_lockgroup = this->GetArgInt (++i); }
836  else if (has_value && (attr == "shortlimit" || attr == "short_limit")) { hook.option_min_range_meters = this->GetArgFloat(++i); }
837  // Flags
838  else if ((attr == "selflock") ||(attr == "self-lock") ||(attr == "self_lock") ) { BITMASK_SET_1(hook.flags, Hook::FLAG_SELF_LOCK); }
839  else if ((attr == "autolock") ||(attr == "auto-lock") ||(attr == "auto_lock") ) { BITMASK_SET_1(hook.flags, Hook::FLAG_AUTO_LOCK); }
840  else if ((attr == "nodisable")||(attr == "no-disable")||(attr == "no_disable")) { BITMASK_SET_1(hook.flags, Hook::FLAG_NO_DISABLE); }
841  else if ((attr == "norope") ||(attr == "no-rope") ||(attr == "no_rope") ) { BITMASK_SET_1(hook.flags, Hook::FLAG_NO_ROPE); }
842  else if ((attr == "visible") ||(attr == "vis") ) { BITMASK_SET_1(hook.flags, Hook::FLAG_VISIBLE); }
843  else
844  {
845  std::string msg = "Ignoring invalid option: " + attr;
846  this->AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, msg.c_str());
847  }
848  i++;
849  }
850 
851  m_current_module->hooks.push_back(hook);
852 }

989 void Parser::ParseSubmesh()

1003  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < options_str.length(); i++)
1004  {

1007  case 'c': cab.options |= Cab::OPTION_c_CONTACT; break;
1008  case 'b': cab.options |= Cab::OPTION_b_BUOYANT; break;

1013  case 'S': cab.options |= (Cab::OPTION_u_INVULNERABLE | Cab::OPTION_b_BUOYANT); break;
1014  case 'n': break; // Placeholder, does nothing
1015

1017  char msg[200] = "";
1018  snprintf(msg, 200, "'submesh/cab' Ignoring invalid option '%c'...", options_str.at(i));
1019  this->AddMessage(Message::TYPE_WARNING, msg);
1020  break;
1021  }
1022  }
1023  }
1024

1026  }
1027  else if (m_current_subsection == File::SUBSECTION__SUBMESH__TEXCOORDS)
1028  {

1044 void Parser::ParseFlexbody()
1045 {
1046  if (m_current_subsection == File::SUBSECTION__FLEXBODIES__PROPLIKE_LINE)
1047  {
1048  if (! this->CheckNumArguments(10)) { return; }
1049 
1050  Flexbody flexbody;
1051  flexbody.reference_node = this->GetArgNodeRef (0);
1052  flexbody.x_axis_node = this->GetArgNodeRef (1);
1053  flexbody.y_axis_node = this->GetArgNodeRef (2);
1054  flexbody.offset.x = this->GetArgFloat (3);
1055  flexbody.offset.y = this->GetArgFloat (4);
1056  flexbody.offset.z = this->GetArgFloat (5);
1057  flexbody.rotation.x = this->GetArgFloat (6);
1058  flexbody.rotation.y = this->GetArgFloat (7);
1059  flexbody.rotation.z = this->GetArgFloat (8);
1060  flexbody.mesh_name = this->GetArgStr (9);
1061 
1062  m_last_flexbody = std::shared_ptr<Flexbody>( new Flexbody(flexbody) );
1063  m_current_module->flexbodies.push_back(m_last_flexbody);
1064 
1065  // Switch subsection
1066  m_current_subsection = File::SUBSECTION__FLEXBODIES__FORSET_LINE;
1067  }
1068  else if (m_current_subsection == File::SUBSECTION__FLEXBODIES__FORSET_LINE)
1069  {
1070  // Syntax: "forset", followed by space/comma, followed by ","-separated items.
1071  // Acceptable item forms:
1072  // * Single node number / node name
1073  // * Pair of node numbers:" 123 - 456 ". Whitespace is optional.
1074 
1075  char setdef[LINE_BUFFER_LENGTH] = ""; // strtok() is destructive, we need own buffer.
1076  strncpy(setdef, m_current_line + 6, LINE_BUFFER_LENGTH - 6); // Cut away "forset"
1077  const char* item = std::strtok(setdef, ",");
1078 
1079  // TODO: Add error reporting
1080  // It appears strtoul() sets no ERRNO for input 'x1' (parsed -> '0')
1081 
1082  const ptrdiff_t MAX_ITEM_LEN = 200;
1083  while (item != nullptr)
1084  {
1085  const char* hyphen = strchr(item, '-');
1086  if (hyphen != nullptr)
1087  {
1088  unsigned a = 0;
1089  char* a_end = nullptr;
1090  std::string a_text;
1091  std::string b_text;
1092  if (hyphen != item)
1093  {
1094  a = ::strtoul(item, &a_end, 10);
1095  size_t length = std::min(a_end - item, MAX_ITEM_LEN);
1096  a_text = std::string(item, length);
1097  }
1098  char* b_end = nullptr;
1099  const char* item2 = hyphen + 1;
1100  unsigned b = ::strtoul(item2, &b_end, 10);
1101  size_t length = std::min(b_end - item2, MAX_ITEM_LEN);
1102  b_text = std::string(item2, length);
1103 
1104  // Add interval [a-b]
1105  m_last_flexbody->node_list_to_import.push_back(
1106  Node::Range(
1107  Node::Ref(a_text, a, Node::Ref::IMPORT_STATE_IS_VALID, m_current_line_number),
1108  Node::Ref(b_text, b, Node::Ref::IMPORT_STATE_IS_VALID, m_current_line_number)));
1109  }
1110  else
1111  {
1112  errno = 0;
1113  unsigned a = 0;
1114  a = ::strtoul(item, nullptr, 10);
1115  // Add interval [a-a]
1116  Node::Range range_a = Node::Range(Node::Ref(std::string(item), a, Node::Ref::IMPORT_STATE_IS_VALID, m_current_line_number));
1117  m_last_flexbody->node_list_to_import.push_back(range_a);
1118  }
1119  item = strtok(nullptr, ",");
1120  }
1121 
1122  // Switch subsection
1123  m_current_subsection = File::SUBSECTION__FLEXBODIES__PROPLIKE_LINE;
1124  }
1125  else
1126  {
1127  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_FATAL_ERROR, "Internal parser failure, section 'flexbodies' not parsed.");
1128  }
1129 }

1556 void Parser::ParseCommandsUnified()
1557 {
1558  const bool is_commands2 = (m_current_section == File::SECTION_COMMANDS_2);
1559  const int max_args = (is_commands2 ? 8 : 7);
1560  if (! this->CheckNumArguments(max_args)) { return; }
1561 
1562  Command2 command2;
1563  command2.beam_defaults = m_user_beam_defaults;
1564  command2.detacher_group = m_current_detacher_group;
1565  command2._format_version = (is_commands2) ? 2 : 1;
1566  command2.inertia_defaults = m_user_default_inertia;
1567 
1568  int pos = 0;
1569  command2.nodes[0] = this->GetArgNodeRef(pos++);
1570  command2.nodes[1] = this->GetArgNodeRef(pos++);
1571  command2.shorten_rate = this->GetArgFloat (pos++);
1572 
1573  if (is_commands2)
1574  {
1575  command2.lengthen_rate = this->GetArgFloat(pos++);
1576  }
1577  else
1578  {
1579  command2.lengthen_rate = command2.shorten_rate;
1580  }
1581 
1582  command2.max_contraction = this->GetArgFloat(pos++);
1583  command2.max_extension = this->GetArgFloat(pos++);
1584  command2.contract_key = this->GetArgInt (pos++);
1585  command2.extend_key = this->GetArgInt (pos++);
1586 
1587  if (m_num_args <= max_args) // No more args?
1588  {
1589  m_current_module->commands_2.push_back(command2);
1590  return;
1591  }
1592 
1593  // Parse options
1594  const int WARN_LEN = 200;
1595  char warn_msg[WARN_LEN] = "";
1596  std::string options_str = this->GetArgStr(pos++);
1597  char winner = 0;
1598  for (auto itor = options_str.begin(); itor != options_str.end(); ++itor)
1599  {
1600  const char c = *itor;
1601  if ((winner == 0) && (c == 'o' || c == 'p' || c == 'c')) { winner = c; }
1602 
1603  if (c == 'n') {} // Filler, does nothing
1604  else if (c == 'i') { command2.option_i_invisible = true; }
1605  else if (c == 'r') { command2.option_r_rope = true; }
1606  else if (c == 'f') { command2.option_f_not_faster = true; }
1607  else if (c == 'c') { command2.option_c_auto_center = true; }
1608  else if (c == 'p') { command2.option_p_1press = true; }
1609  else if (c == 'o') { command2.option_o_1press_center = true; }
1610  else
1611  {
1612  snprintf(warn_msg, WARN_LEN, "Ignoring unknown flag '%c'", c);
1613  this->AddMessage(Message::TYPE_WARNING, warn_msg);
1614  }
1615  }
1616 
1617  // Resolve option conflicts
1618  if (command2.option_c_auto_center && winner != 'c' && winner != 0)
1619  {
1620  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Command cannot be one-pressed and self centering at the same time, ignoring flag 'c'");
1621  command2.option_c_auto_center = false;
1622  }
1623  char ignored = '\0';
1624  if (command2.option_o_1press_center && winner != 'o' && winner != 0)
1625  {
1626  command2.option_o_1press_center = false;
1627  ignored = 'o';
1628  }
1629  else if (command2.option_p_1press && winner != 'p' && winner != 0)
1630  {
1631  command2.option_p_1press = false;
1632  ignored = 'p';
1633  }
1634 
1635  // Report conflicts
1636  if (ignored != 0 && winner == 'c')
1637  {
1638  snprintf(warn_msg, WARN_LEN, "Command cannot be one-pressed and self centering at the same time, ignoring flag '%c'", ignored);
1639  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_WARNING, warn_msg);
1640  }
1641  else if (ignored != 0 && (winner == 'o' || winner == 'p'))
1642  {
1643  snprintf(warn_msg, WARN_LEN, "Command already has a one-pressed c.mode, ignoring flag '%c'", ignored);
1644  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_WARNING, warn_msg);
1645  }
1646 
1647  if (m_num_args > pos) { command2.description = this->GetArgStr (pos++);}
1648 
1649  if (m_num_args > pos) { ParseOptionalInertia(command2.inertia, pos); pos += 4; }
1650 
1651  if (m_num_args > pos) { command2.affect_engine = this->GetArgFloat(pos++);}
1652  if (m_num_args > pos) { command2.needs_engine = this->GetArgBool (pos++);}
1653  if (m_num_args > pos) { command2.plays_sound = this->GetArgBool (pos++);}
1654 
1655  m_current_module->commands_2.push_back(command2);
1656 }

1734 void Parser::ParseAxles()
1735 {
1736  Axle axle;
1737 
1738  Ogre::StringVector tokens = Ogre::StringUtil::split(m_current_line, ",");
1739  Ogre::StringVector::iterator iter = tokens.begin();
1740  for ( ; iter != tokens.end(); iter++)
1741  {
1742  std::smatch results;
1743  if (! std::regex_search(*iter, results, Regexes::SECTION_AXLES_PROPERTY))
1744  {
1745  this->AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Invalid property, ignoring whole line...");
1746  return;
1747  }
1748  // NOTE: Positions in 'results' array match E_CAPTURE*() positions (starting with 1) in the respective regex.
1749 
1750  if (results[1].matched)
1751  {
1752  unsigned int wheel_index = STR_PARSE_INT(results[2]) - 1;
1753  axle.wheels[wheel_index][0] = _ParseNodeRef(results[3]);
1754  axle.wheels[wheel_index][1] = _ParseNodeRef(results[4]);
1755  }
1756  else if (results[5].matched)
1757  {
1758  std::string options_str = results[6].str();
1759  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < options_str.length(); i++)
1760  {
1761  switch(options_str.at(i))
1762  {
1763  case 'o':
1764  axle.options.push_back(Axle::OPTION_o_OPEN);
1765  break;
1766  case 'l':
1767  axle.options.push_back(Axle::OPTION_l_LOCKED);
1768  break;
1769  case 's':
1770  axle.options.push_back(Axle::OPTION_s_SPLIT);
1771  break;
1772 
1773  default: // No check needed, regex takes care of that
1774  break;
1775  }
1776  }
1777  }
1778  }
1779 
1780  m_current_module->axles.push_back(axle);
1781 }

1897 void Parser::ParseTriggers()
1898 {
1899  if (! this->CheckNumArguments(6)) { return; }
1900 
1901  Trigger trigger;
1902  trigger.beam_defaults = m_user_beam_defaults;
1903  trigger.detacher_group = m_current_detacher_group;
1904  trigger.nodes[0] = this->GetArgNodeRef(0);
1905  trigger.nodes[1] = this->GetArgNodeRef(1);
1906  trigger.contraction_trigger_limit = this->GetArgFloat (2);
1907  trigger.expansion_trigger_limit = this->GetArgFloat (3);
1908 
1909  int shortbound_trigger_action = this->GetArgInt(4);
1910  int longbound_trigger_action = this->GetArgInt(5);
1911  if (m_num_args > 6)
1912  {
1913  std::string options_str = this->GetArgStr(6);
1914  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < options_str.length(); i++)
1915  {
1916  switch(options_str.at(i))
1917  {
1918  case 'i': trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_i_INVISIBLE; break;
1919  case 'c': trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_c_COMMAND_STYLE; break;
1920  case 'x': trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_x_START_OFF; break;
1921  case 'b': trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_b_BLOCK_KEYS; break;
1922  case 'B': trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_B_BLOCK_TRIGGERS; break;
1923  case 'A': trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_A_INV_BLOCK_TRIGGERS; break;
1924  case 's': trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_s_SWITCH_CMD_NUM; break;
1925  case 'h': trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_h_UNLOCK_HOOKGROUPS_KEY; break;
1926  case 'H': trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_H_LOCK_HOOKGROUPS_KEY; break;
1927  case 't': trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_t_CONTINUOUS; break;
1928  case 'E': trigger.options |= Trigger::OPTION_E_ENGINE_TRIGGER; break;
1929 
1930  default:
1931  this->AddMessage(Message::TYPE_WARNING, Ogre::String("Invalid trigger option: " + options_str.at(i)));
1932  }
1933  }
1934  }
1935 
1936  if (m_num_args > 7)
1937  {
1938  float boundary_timer = this->GetArgFloat(7);
1939  if (boundary_timer > 0.0f)
1940  trigger.boundary_timer = boundary_timer;
1941  }
1942 
1943  // Handle actions
1944  if (trigger.IsHookToggleTrigger())
1945  {
1946  Trigger::HookToggleTrigger hook_toggle;
1947  hook_toggle.contraction_trigger_hookgroup_id = shortbound_trigger_action;
1948  hook_toggle.extension_trigger_hookgroup_id = longbound_trigger_action;
1949  trigger.SetHookToggleTrigger(hook_toggle);
1950  }
1951  else if (trigger.HasFlag_E_EngineTrigger())
1952  {
1953  Trigger::EngineTrigger engine_trigger;
1954  engine_trigger.function = Trigger::EngineTrigger::Function(shortbound_trigger_action);
1955  engine_trigger.motor_index = longbound_trigger_action;
1956  trigger.SetEngineTrigger(engine_trigger);
1957  }
1958  else
1959  {
1960  Trigger::CommandKeyTrigger command_keys;
1961  command_keys.contraction_trigger_key = shortbound_trigger_action;
1962  command_keys.extension_trigger_key = longbound_trigger_action;
1963  trigger.SetCommandKeyTrigger(command_keys);
1964  }
1965 
1966  m_current_module->triggers.push_back(trigger);
1967 }

2085  in_rail_node_list = false;

2089  in_rail_node_list = false;

2247 Node::Ref Parser::_ParseNodeRef(std::string const & node_id_str)
2248 {
2249  if (m_sequential_importer.IsEnabled())
2250  {
2251  // Import of legacy fileformatversion
2252  int node_id_num = STR_PARSE_INT(node_id_str);
2253  if (node_id_num < 0)
2254  {
2255  std::stringstream msg;
2256  msg << "Encountered node with illegal negative number: '" << node_id_num
2257  << "', parsing as positive '" << node_id_num * -1 << "' for backwards compatibility. Please fix as soon as possible.";
2258  AddMessage(node_id_str, Message::TYPE_WARNING, msg.str());
2259  node_id_num *= -1;
2260  }
2261  // Since fileformatversion is not known from the beginning of parsing, 2 states must be kept
2262  // at the same time: IMPORT_STATE and REGULAR_STATE. The outer logic must make the right pick.
2263  unsigned int flags = Node::Ref::IMPORT_STATE_IS_VALID | // Import state
2264  Node::Ref::REGULAR_STATE_IS_VALID | Node::Ref::REGULAR_STATE_IS_NAMED; // Regular state (fileformatversion >= 450)
2265  if (m_any_named_node_defined)
2266  {
2267  flags |= Node::Ref::IMPORT_STATE_MUST_CHECK_NAMED_FIRST;
2268  }
2269  return Node::Ref(node_id_str, node_id_num, flags, m_current_line_number);
2270  }
2271  else
2272  {
2273  // fileformatversion >= 450, use named-only nodes
2274  return Node::Ref(node_id_str, 0, Node::Ref::REGULAR_STATE_IS_VALID | Node::Ref::REGULAR_STATE_IS_NAMED, m_current_line_number);

2516 void Parser::_TrimTrailingComments(std::string const & line_in, std::string & line_out)
2517 {

2520  int comment_start = line_in.find_first_of(";");
2521  if (comment_start != Ogre::String::npos)
2522  {
2523  line_out = line_in.substr(0, comment_start);
2524  return;
2525  }
2526  // The [//Comment] is harder - the '/' character may also be present in DESCRIPTION arguments!
2527  comment_start = line_in.find_last_of("/");
2528  if (comment_start != Ogre::String::npos)
2529  {
2530  while (comment_start >= 0)
2531  {
2532  char c = line_in[comment_start - 1];
2533  if (c != '/' && c != ' ' && c != '\t')
2534  {
2535  break; // Start of comment found
2536  }
2537  --comment_start;
2538  }
2539  line_out = line_in.substr(0, comment_start);
2540  return;
2541  }
2542  // No comment found
2543  line_out = line_in;
2544 }

2994 File::Keyword Parser::IdentifyKeywordInCurrentLine()
2995 {
2996  // Quick check - keyword always starts with ASCII letter
2997  char c = m_current_line[0]; // Note: line comes in trimmed
2998  if (! ((c >= 'a' && c <= 'z') || (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z')))
2999  {
3000  return File::KEYWORD_INVALID;
3001  }
3002 
3003  // Search with correct lettercase
3004  std::smatch results;
3005  std::string line(m_current_line);
3006  std::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::IDENTIFY_KEYWORD_RESPECT_CASE); // Always returns true.
3007  File::Keyword keyword = FindKeywordMatch(results);
3008  if (keyword != File::KEYWORD_INVALID)
3009  {
3010  return keyword;
3011  }
3012 
3013  // Search and ignore lettercase
3014  std::regex_search(line, results, Regexes::IDENTIFY_KEYWORD_IGNORE_CASE); // Always returns true.
3015  keyword = FindKeywordMatch(results);
3016  if (keyword != File::KEYWORD_INVALID)
3017  {
3018  this->AddMessage(line, Message::TYPE_WARNING,
3019  "Keyword has invalid lettercase. Correct form is: " + std::string(File::KeywordToString(keyword)));
3020  }
3021  return keyword;
3022 }
3023 
3024 File::Keyword Parser::FindKeywordMatch(std::smatch& search_results)
3025 {
3026  // The 'results' array contains a complete match at positon [0] and sub-matches starting with [1],

3465 int Parser::TokenizeCurrentLine()
3466 {

3468  const char* cur_char = m_current_line;
3469  int arg_len = 0;
3470  while ((*cur_char != '\0') && (cur_arg < Parser::LINE_MAX_ARGS))
3471  {
3472  const bool is_arg = !IsSeparator(*cur_char);
3473  if ((arg_len == 0) && is_arg)
3474  {
3475  m_args[cur_arg].start = cur_char;
3476  arg_len = 1;
3477  }
3478  else if ((arg_len > 0) && !is_arg)
3479  {
3480  m_args[cur_arg].length = arg_len;
3481  arg_len = 0;
3482  ++cur_arg;
3483  }
3484  else if (is_arg)
3485  {
3486  ++arg_len;
3487  }
3488  ++cur_char;
3489  }
3490  if (arg_len > 0)
3491  {
3492  m_args[cur_arg].length = arg_len;
3493  ++cur_arg;
